body:
var ${1:config} = {
	mark: '',
	port: 4848,
	appname: '',
	host: '',
	prefix: '',
	origin: '',
	isSecure: true|false,
	rejectUnauthorized: true|false,
	headers: ''|{},
	ticket: ''|false,
	key: ''|null,
	cert: ''|null,
	ca: ''|null,
	pfx: ''|null,
	passphrase: ''|null,
	identity: '',
	debug: true|false,
	disconnect: ''
}

MakeWeekDate.description: This function returns a date calculated from the year YYYY, the week WW and the day-of-week D.

HideSuffix.description: All field names ending with this text string will be hidden in the same manner as the system fields. This is a user-defined variable.

HidePrefix.description: All field names beginning with this text string will be hidden in the same manner as the system fields. This is a user-defined variable.

YearToDate.description: This function finds if the input date falls within the year of the date the script was last loaded, and returns True if it does, False if it does not.

YearStart.description: This function returns a timestamp corresponding to the start of the first day of the year containing date. The default output format will be the DateFormat set in the script.

YearName.description: This function returns a four-digit year as display value with an underlying numeric value corresponding to a timestamp of the first millisecond of the first day of the year containing date.
